kubernetes fsGroup already does this activity if fsGroup is configured. And it will be configured because we are using "common.podSecurityContext" which creates it using group_id 

{{- define "common.podSecurityContext" -}}
securityContext:
  runAsUser: {{ .Values.securityContext.user_id }}
  runAsGroup: {{ .Values.securityContext.group_id }}
  fsGroup: {{ .Values.securityContext.group_id }}
{{- end }}

Therefore init-container is not required.
